# Intentionally empty of SPA catch-alls.
#
# Cloudflare Pages already serves index.html for unknown app routes when there
# is no top-level 404.html. A `/* /index.html 200` rule also rewrote *missing*
# /assets/* hashes to index.html with status 200 and Content-Type text/html.
# Browsers then refused to apply the "stylesheet" (or execute the module),
# which shows up as a white page with unstyled black text — especially on
# mobile tabs that outlive a deploy.
#
# public/assets/404.html makes missing hashed assets return a real 404 instead.
